Akwa Ibom State Government has spoken of the readiness of Ibom Air to commence commercial flight operations across Nigeria before the swearing-in of Governor Udom Emmanuel for the second term on May 29. The government also noted that the renovated General Hospital, Equita in Oron, Immanuel General Hospital in Eket, Awa Cottage Hospital and road projects under construction are also billed for commissioning before May 29.  The governor, who spoke through the state Commissioner for Information and Strategy, Mr. Charles Udoh, yesterday during an interactive session with newsmen in Uyo, the state capital, said the breakthroughs were indications that Governor Emmanuel’s  administration is committed to the development of Akwa Ibom State, as the day-to-day running of government as well as all development processes of the government in all sectors, were on course throughout the period of electioneering campaign for the reelection of the governor.  Udoh, who debunked the insinuations that the state funds were spent for the re-election, wondered where the funds spent on the projects to be commissioned came from, even as